{
  "assumptions": [
    "Traffic ~<1k/month — extremely low volume; serverless-no-VPC is the correct floor (near-zero idle cost).",
    "TradingView sends webhook POSTs with a shared secret in the payload or header for HMAC/token verification.",
    "Downstream targets (existing graph + table display) are reached via HTTP or a known AWS integration — modeled as an external HTTP destination and DynamoDB (canonical store for later AI step).",
    "'Pushes data where it needs to go' = persist the raw signal + fan-out to the existing frontend via HTTP callback / EventBridge.",
    "The 'AI step' (Python evaluation, not in scope now) is pre-wired as a stub Lambda + S3 data lake so the architecture is ready without building it today.",
    "No PII or regulated data — no HIPAA/PCI scope.",
    "Downtime tolerance of 'a few minutes' maps to budget single-AZ serverless (Lambda is multi-AZ by default within a region, so even budget tier is highly available here).",
    "Cost estimates are on-demand list prices for us-east-1, presented as ranges over assumed monthly volumes. They exclude the AWS Free Tier, Savings Plans, Reserved Instances, and negotiated discounts.",
    "Assumed traffic ~100k–1M requests/month, applied equally to all three tiers (tiers differ by robustness, not traffic). Set \"expected monthly visitors\" in intake to change it."
  ],
  "clarificationsUsed": [
    "Downtime tolerance: best-effort, a few minutes acceptable → single-AZ budget tier is fine; Lambda's regional multi-AZ default satisfies this anyway.",
    "No PII/regulated data → no compliance-scoping keyDecision needed.",
    "Traffic <1k/month → serverless on-demand, no provisioned capacity anywhere; idle cost ~$0."
  ],
