      "delta": [
        "Baseline: fully serverless, no VPC, no NAT gateway, near-zero idle cost at <1k/mo.",
        "Single Lambda concurrency reservation (10) absorbs all realistic burst without over-provisioning.",
        "DynamoDB on-demand: zero capacity planning, instant scale.",
        "SQS + DLQ decouples ingest from frontend delivery; retries absorb transient downstream failures.",
        "S3 data lake stub wired now via DynamoDB Streams — AI step can be dropped in without rearchitecting.",
        "Observability: CloudWatch logs + alarms on error rate / DLQ depth / latency → SNS email."
      ],
      "tradeoffs": [
        "No multi-AZ explicit redundancy beyond Lambda's default regional distribution — acceptable at best-effort tolerance.",
        "No SQS FIFO: standard queue may deliver out-of-order at very high burst (irrelevant at <1k/mo).",
        "Bearer token auth is weaker than HMAC but is the ceiling of TradingView's capability.",
        "Single CloudFront distribution adds ~10–20ms latency vs direct API GW, offset by WAF coverage."
      ],
